# OneNote MCP Server — environment example
# Copy to .env and fill in values.

# --- Transport ---
# PORT=8000
# HOST=0.0.0.0

# --- Microsoft Graph (choose one auth mode) ---

# Option A: Delegated (interactive browser login) — REQUIRED:
#   - AZURE_CLIENT_ID (and optionally AZURE_TENANT_ID, AZURE_REDIRECT_URI).
#   - Azure: API permissions → Delegated: Notes.Read, User.Read.
#   - Authentication → Add platform → Mobile and desktop apps →
#     Redirect URI must match AZURE_REDIRECT_URI → Allow public client flows = Yes.
#   - Enterprise: if you see "Need admin approval", ask your admin to grant consent for this app.
# AZURE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id
# AZURE_TENANT_ID=your-tenant-id
# AZURE_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:8400

# Option B: Application (service principal) — set all and ONENOTE_USER_ID.
# AZURE_TENANT_ID=your-tenant-id
# AZURE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id
# AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret
# ONENOTE_USER_ID=user-object-id-or-upn
